rt from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."],"variants":[{"name":"Roger","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."]}]},{"name":"Clarke","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which originated as an occupational name denoting a clerk (Latin <i>clericus</i>), in the Middle Ages a man in minor holy orders who earned his living by his ability to read and write. It is recorded as a given name in Britain from the late 17th century onwards. Since the 1930s, when it was associated particularly with the film star  Clark Gable  (  1901–60 ), it has been widely used as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":24,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":33,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Rodgerus Rodger Clarke Woodchurch was born in 1191, in Ashford, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir Anketillus Clarke Woodchurch II. He married Lady Isabella Wakehurst de Woodchurch about 1216, in Woodchurch, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1243, in his hometown, at the age of 52, and was buried in England."},"et":{"1191–1243":"1191–1243","1198–1260":"1198–1260","1216–1286":"1216–1286","1219–Female":"1219–Surnud","1222–1242":"1222–1242","1166–1191":"1166–1191","before 1700":"before 1700","1219   ":"1219","1242":"1242","1286":"1286","1198":"1198","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","ABT 1242":"umbes 1242","1224":"1224","1222":"1222","about 1216":"umbes 1216","1243":"1243","1166":"1166","1219":"1219","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Woodchurch, Cheshire, England":"Woodchurch, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","United Kingdom":"United Kingdom","Ashford, Kent, England":"Ashford, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woodchurch, Kent, England":"Woodchurch, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1191–1243":"1191–1243","1198–1260":"1198–1260","1216–1286":"1216–1286","1219–Female":"1219–Kuollut","1222–1242":"1222–1242","1166–1191":"1166–1191","before 1700":"ennen vuotta 1700","1219   ":"1219","1242":"1242","1286":"1286","1198":"1198","1260":"1260","1191":"1191","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","ABT 1242":"noin 1242","1224":"1224","1222":"1222","about 1216":"noin 1216","1243":"1243","1166":"1166","1219":"1219","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Woodchurch, Cheshire, England":"Woodchurch, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","U